label: uncl2379
comment: Code specifying the representation of a date, time or period.

values.label: DDMMYY
values.comment: Calendar date: D = Day; M = Month; Y = Year.

values.label: MMDDYY
values.comment: Calendar date: M = Month; D = Day; Y = Year.

values.label: DDMMCCYY
values.comment: Calendar date C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day.

values.label: DDMMCCYYHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date and time: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day; H=Hour; M=Minute.

values.label: CCYYMMB
values.comment: Half-month: CC=century YY=year MM=month, B=1:first half month, B=2:second half month.

values.label: CCYYMMW
values.comment: Week within a calendar month: CC=century YY=year MM=month. W=1-5 first week to fifth week in a month.

values.label: CCYYMMDDS
values.comment: Shift within a calendar day: CC=century YY=year MM=month DD=day S=1-9 shift in a day.

values.label: CCYYMMDDPP
values.comment: Time period within a calendar day: CC=century YY=year MM=month DD=day PP=00-99 time period.

values.label: CCYYMMDDTHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time with minutes: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day; T=Time designator; H=Hour; M=Minutes.  The character [T] shall be used as time designator to indicate the start of the representation of the time. For example: 20010912T1433.

values.label: YYMMDD
values.comment: Calendar date: Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day.

values.label: CCYYMMDD
values.comment: Calendar date: C = Century ; Y = Year ; M = Month ; D = Day.

values.label: YYWWD
values.comment: Calendar week day: Y = Year ; W = Week ; D = Day Week number 01 is always first week of January Day number 1 is always Monday.

values.label: MMWW-MMWW
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start week of a month followed by the end week of a month. Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYDDD
values.comment: Calendar day: Y = Year ; D = Day January the first = Day 001 Always start numbering the days of the year from January 1st through December 31st.

values.label: MMDD
values.comment: Day of a month: M = Month; D = Day.

values.label: DDD
values.comment: Day's number within a specific year: D = Day.

values.label: WW
values.comment: Week's number within a specific year: W = Week.

values.label: MM
values.comment: Month's number within a specific year: M = Month.

values.label: DD
values.comment: Day's number within is a specific month: D = Day.

values.label: YYMMDDHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time without seconds: Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

values.label: YYMMDDHHMMSS
values.comment: Calendar date including time with seconds: Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; m = Minutes = Seconds.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time with minutes: C=Century; Y=Year; M=Month; D=Day; H=Hour; M=Minutes.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMSS
values.comment: Calendar date including time with seconds: C=Century;Y=Year; M=Month;D=Day;H=Hour;M=Minute;S=Second.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMZHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time and time zone expressed in hours and minutes. ZHHMM = time zone given as offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).

values.label: YYMMDDHHMMZHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time without seconds, with Time Zone:  Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute,  Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

values.label: YYMMDDHHMMSSZHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time with seconds, with Time Zone:  Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute, S = Seconds Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMSSZHHMM
values.comment: Calendar date including time with seconds, with Time Zone:  C = Century, Y = Year; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute, S = Seconds, Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

values.label: HHMMSSZHHMM
values.comment: Time with seconds and with Time Zone:  H = Hour; M = Minute, S = Seconds, Z = leading plus/minus sign, HHMM = difference to UTC in Hours and Minutes.

values.label: HHMMSSZHHMM-HHMMSSZHHMM
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (both expressed by hours, minutes, seconds and time zone leading plus/minus sign and time zone difference in hours and minutes).

values.label: YYMMDDHHMMZZZ
values.comment: See 201 + Z = Time zone.

values.label: YYMMDDHHMMSSZZZ
values.comment: See 202 + Z = Time zone.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMZZZ
values.comment: See 203 plus Z=Time zone.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMSSZZZ
values.comment: See 204 plus Z=Time zone.

values.label: MMDDHHMM
values.comment: Month, day, hours, minutes; M = Month; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

values.label: DDHHMM
values.comment: Day, hours, minutes; D = Day; H = Hour; M = Minute.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMSSFFF
values.comment: Calendar date including time with seconds and milliseconds C = century, Y = year, M = month, D = day, H = hour, M = minute, S = second, F = millisecond.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMMZZZ-CCYYMMDDHHMMZZZ
values.comment: A period of time which includes the century, year, month, day, hour and minute and time zone. Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

values.label: HHMM
values.comment: Time without seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute.

values.label: HHMMSS
values.comment: Time with seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute; s = Seconds.

values.label: HHMMSSZZZ
values.comment: See 402 plus Z=Time zone.

values.label: MMMMSS
values.comment: Time without hours: m=minutes, s=seconds.

values.label: ZHHMM
values.comment: Offset from Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) where Z is plus (+) or minus (-).

values.label: HHMMHHMM
values.comment: Time span without seconds: H = Hour; m = Minute;.

values.label: HHMMSS-HHMMSS
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (both expressed by hours minutes and seconds). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: HHMMSSZZZ-HHMMSSZZZ
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (both expressed by hours minutes, seconds and time zone). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CC
values.comment: Century.

values.label: YY
values.comment: Calendar year: Y = Year.

values.label: CCYY
values.comment: Calendar year including century: C = Century; Y = Year.

values.label: YYS
values.comment: Semester in a calendar year: Y = Year; S = Semester.

values.label: CCYYS
values.comment: Semester in a calendar year: C = Century; Y = Year; S = Semester.

values.label: CCYYQ
values.comment: Quarter in a calendar year: C = Century; Y = Year; Q = Quarter.

values.label: YYMM
values.comment: Month within a calendar year: Y = Year; M = Month.

values.label: CCYYMM
values.comment: Month within a calendar year: CC = Century; Y = Year; M = Month.

values.label: YYMMA
values.comment: To specifiy a ten-day period within a month of a year (A = ten day period).

values.label: CCYYMMA
values.comment: To specifiy a ten-day period within a month of a year, including century  (A = ten day period).

values.label: YYWW
values.comment: Week within a calendar year: Y = Year; W = Week 1st week of January = week 01.

values.label: CCYYWW
values.comment: Week within a calendar year: CC = Century; Y = Year; W = Week (1st week of January = week 01).

values.label: YY-YY
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start year followed by the end year (both without century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYY-CCYY
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start year followed by the end year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYS-YYS
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start semester of a year followed by the end semester of a year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYYS-CCYYS
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start semester of a year followed by the end semester of a year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYPYYP
values.comment: Format of period to be given without hyphen (P = period of 4 months).

values.label: CCYYP-CCYYP
values.comment: Format of period to be given without hyphen (P = period of 4 months).

values.label: YYQ-YYQ
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start quarter of a year followed by the end quarter of year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYYQ-CCYYQ
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start quarter of a year followed by the end quarter of year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYMM-YYMM
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start month of a year followed by the end month of a year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYYMM-CCYYMM
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start month of a year followed by the end month of a year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYMMDDHHMM-YYMMDDHHMM
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start time followed by the end time (format year, month, day, hour and minute). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYWW-YYWW
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start week of a year followed by the end week of year (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYYWW-CCYYWW
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start week of a year followed by the end week of year (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: YYMMDD-YYMMDD
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start date followed by the end date (both not including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYYMMDD-CCYYMMDD
values.comment: A period of time specified by giving the start date followed by the end date (both including century). Data is to be transmitted as consecutive characters without hyphen.

values.label: CCYYMMDDHHMM-CCYYMMDDHHMM
values.comment: A period of time which includes the century, year, month, day, hour and minute. Format of period to be given in actual message without hyphen.

values.label: DHHMM-DHHMM
values.comment: Format of period to be given without hyphen (D=day of the week, 1=Monday; 2=Tuesday; ... 7=Sunday).

values.label: Year
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of years.

values.label: Month
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of months.

values.label: Week
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of weeks.

values.label: Day
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of days.

values.label: Hour
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of hours.

values.label: Minute
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of minutes.

values.label: Second
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of seconds.

values.label: Semester
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of semesters (six months).

values.label: Four months period
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of four months periods.

values.label: Trimester
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of trimesters (three months).

values.label: Half month
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of half months.

values.label: Ten days
values.comment: To indicate a quantity of ten days periods.

values.label: Day of the week
values.comment: Numeric representation of the day (Monday = 1).

values.label: Working days
values.comment: Number of working days.
